# Festag auth — Linear white CTAs

Canonical light-mode CTA (Weiter, SSO, Apple, Docs „Alle anzeigen“, Security CTA):

```css
background: #ffffff;
color: #1e1e20;
border: 1px solid rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.06);   /* soft hairline — not a heavy top bar */
box-shadow: 0 1px 2px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.05); /* soft shadow below only */
```

Hover: `#fafafa` + border `rgba(0,0,0,.09)` + shadow `0 1px 2px rgba(0,0,0,.07)`  
Active: `#f4f4f5` + soft bottom `0 1px 1px rgba(0,0,0,.04)` — **no inset top highlight**

Tokens live on `.al-root` as `--festag-btn-dark-*` so they never inherit portal dark html tokens (that made buttons invisible on white).

## Inputs

No focus rings — fill step only. `outline: none` on `.al-input`.

## Do not

- Dual/heavy marketing shadows
- Borderless white-on-white
- Inset top strokes / `inset 0 1px …` on idle or hover (that reads as a strong top edge)
- Thicker “3D platform” bars (`0 1.5px 0`)
- Re-litigate stroke vs no-stroke — soft Linear hairline + bottom shadow is the lock
